      "modified": "2026-04-13T19:44:29.000Z",
      "name": "Microsoft Patches Four Critical Zero-Days in April Patch Tuesday Including Actively Exploited CLFS Flaw",
      "description": "Microsoft has released its April 2025 Patch Tuesday security update, addressing 147 vulnerabilities across Windows, Office, Azure, and Exchange. Four vulnerabilities are rated Critical, and two are confirmed as being actively exploited in the wild. Most notably, CVE-2025-2891 is a privilege escalation vulnerability in the Windows Common Log File System (CLFS) driver that Microsoft confirms has been exploited in targeted ransomware attacks. The vulnerability allows a local attacker to gain SYSTEM privileges. CVE-2025-3015 is a remote code execution flaw in Microsoft Exchange Server that is being exploited to deploy web shells. Security teams should prioritise patching CLFS and Exchange systems immediately. The remaining critical patches cover vulnerabilities in SharePoint, Remote Desktop Services, and the Windows DNS Server.",
      "published": "2025-04-08T18:00:00.000Z",
